abstract: A Trump administration immigration policy that requires asylum seekers to wait in Mexico while their cases wind through U.S. courts was blocked and then reinstated by a court in the matter of hours, creating chaos at border crossings, courtrooms and legal offices.
snippet: A Trump administration immigration policy that requires asylum seekers to wait in Mexico while their cases wind through U.S. courts was blocked and then reinstated by a court in the matter of hours, creating chaos at border crossings, courtrooms a...
lead_paragraph: SAN DIEGO — A Trump administration immigration policy that requires asylum seekers to wait in Mexico while their cases wind through U.S. courts was blocked and then reinstated by a court in the matter of hours, creating chaos at border crossings, courtrooms and legal offices.
headline_main: Court Halts Trump Asylum Policy, Then Suspends Its Own Order
headline_print_headline: Court Halts Trump Asylum Policy, Then Suspends Its Own Order

abstract: How Democratic voters feel about Bernie Sanders’s views on foreign policy and socialist governments tends to split along generational lines.
snippet: How Democratic voters feel about Bernie Sanders’s views on foreign policy and socialist governments tends to split along generational lines.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — In the spring of 1989, as the outgoing mayor of Burlington, Vt., Bernie Sanders and his wife, Jane, traveled to Cuba on an eight-day trip, with the hopes of meeting the Cuban dictator, Fidel Castro.

abstract: The court upheld an injunction blocking a policy that requires asylum applicants to wait in Mexico until their cases are decided. But a stay on the order means the policy could remain in effect.
snippet: The court upheld an injunction blocking a policy that requires asylum applicants to wait in Mexico until their cases are decided. But a stay on the order means the policy could remain in effect.
lead_paragraph: A federal appeals court found a central pillar of the Trump administration’s immigration agenda legally invalid on Friday, ruling that asylum seekers must be allowed into the United States while their cases weave through American immigration courts.

abstract: The legislation, which would ban menthol in all cigarettes, drew opposition from some civil rights groups and African-American lawmakers, who said it could lead to over-policing of their communities.
snippet: The legislation, which would ban menthol in all cigarettes, drew opposition from some civil rights groups and African-American lawmakers, who said it could lead to over-policing of their communities.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House, taking aim at youth vaping and tobacco use, voted Friday to ban the sale of flavored cigarettes and e-cigarette liquids, even as civil rights advocates and some African-American Democrats raised concerns that the legislation unfairly targeted black people.

abstract: A federal appeals court has ruled against a Native American tribe that had been granted sovereign land to build a casino in Massachusetts.

lead_paragraph: BOSTON — A federal appeals court has ruled against a Native American tribe that had been granted sovereign land to build a casino in Massachusetts.
headline_main: Appeals Court Denies Tribe’s Quest for Casino Land
headline_print_headline: Appeals Court Denies Tribe’s Quest for Casino Land

abstract: The U.S. Agriculture Department will make available up to $100 million in grants to expand the infrastructure needed to sell more ethanol, biodiesel and other renewable fuels, the agency announced on Friday.
snippet: The U.S. Agriculture Department will make available up to $100 million in grants to expand the infrastructure needed to sell more ethanol, biodiesel and other renewable fuels, the agency announced on Friday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The U.S. Agriculture Department will make available up to $100 million in grants to expand the infrastructure needed to sell more ethanol, biodiesel and other renewable fuels, the agency announced on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Agriculture Dept to Boost Funds for Biofuel Infrastructure
headline_print_headline: U.S. Agriculture Dept to Boost Funds for Biofuel Infrastructure

abstract: White House Acting Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney on Friday played down the deadly coronavirus that has caused U.S. stock markets to plummet, telling top conservatives that wall-to-wall news coverage of the disease is a ploy to hurt his boss, President Donald Trump.
snippet: White House Acting Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney on Friday played down the deadly coronavirus that has caused U.S. stock markets to plummet, telling top conservatives that wall-to-wall news coverage of the disease is a ploy to hurt his boss, Presid...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — White House Acting Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney on Friday played down the deadly coronavirus that has caused U.S. stock markets to plummet, telling top conservatives that wall-to-wall news coverage of the disease is a ploy to hurt his boss, President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Mulvaney Alleges U.S. Media Is Focusing on Coronavirus to Hurt Trump, Advises Turning Off TV
headline_print_headline: Mulvaney Alleges U.S. Media Is Focusing on Coronavirus to Hurt Trump, Advises Turning Off TV

abstract: The Democrat-controlled U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee on Friday said it is seeking interviews with current and former federal prosecutors who may have knowledge of political meddling in criminal cases, including the four career officials who earlier this month quit the Roger Stone case.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democrat-controlled U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee on Friday said it is seeking interviews with current and former federal prosecutors who may have knowledge of political meddling in criminal cases, including the four career officials who earlier this month quit the Roger Stone case.
headline_main: House Panel Seeks to Interview the Four Career Prosecutors Who Quit Roger Stone Case

abstract: A political advocacy group founded by Bernie Sanders entered into a nondisclosure agreement with an African American political consultant that bars her from discussing a lawsuit alleging racial discrimination at the organization and the Vermont senator's 2016 presidential campaign.

abstract: A Michigan lawmaker who is considering seeking Kwame Kilpatrick’s old job is asking President Donald Trump to grant clemency to Detroit’s imprisoned ex-mayor.
